Making pasta with kids can be so much fun, 🤗 not to mention delicious! 🤤 Watch the full 📹 to see how it’s done, and read on below👇 for the step-by-step instructions! Want to save this for later? 👌 Don’t forget to hit that bookmark button above! 🔖 And if you have any questions at all, drop👇them in the comment section below or DM me!
-
WHAT YOU’LL NEED
• 2 Cups Flour
• 4 Eggs
• Pasta Maker
-
HOW TO
(1) Add 2 cups of flour to a bowl; (2) Make a hole or well in the center of the flour and crack the eggs into it;
(3) Use a fork to slowly stir the egg and flour mixture together;
(4) Knead the dough, first in the bowl, then transfer to a floured surface and continuing kneading;
(5) Add more flour until elastic and not sticky;
(6) Split into 4 pieces and continue to knead;
(7) Roll out the dough, we use a hand crank machine and roll as thin as the second to last setting (the thinest setting often results in pasta that gets stuck together during the cooking process);
(8) Cut the pasta using the pasta-attachment or a knife if you prefer a handcut width!
(9) Boil water and cook the pasta for no more than a few minutes;
(10) Add salt and sauce to taste. Enjoy!
